messages.content: Tell me about this dandiset. *

This Dandiset (DANDI:001354, version draft) is titled **"Hippocampal neuronal responses to programmable antigen-gated G-protein-coupled engineered receptor activation"** by Peter Klein (Stanford University) and collaborators. It contains electrophysiological recordings from mouse hippocampal CA1 neurons, specifically to investigate the effect of programmable antigen-gated G-protein-coupled engineered receptors (“PAGERs”). Key dataset details:

- **Data type:** Single cell electrophysiological recordings (current clamp technique)
- **Organism:** Mus musculus (house mouse)
- **Number of files:** 50 NWB files
- **Number of subjects:** 8 mice
- **Number of cells recorded:** 50
- **Data format:** Neurodata Without Borders (NWB)
- **Experimental protocol:** Activation of hippocampal neurons transfected with PAGER constructs, and responses recorded after applying DCZ (an actuator compound) or DCZ + soluble mCherry.
- **Study aim:** To validate programmable targeting of neuronal activity using engineered GPCRs.
- **Relevant publication:** [Synthetic GPCRs for programmable sensing and control of cell behaviour](https://www.nature.com/articles/s41586-024-08282-3) (Nature, 2024)
- **License:** CC-BY-4.0 (freely reusable with attribution)
